The paper discusses techniques for anonymous user authentication and communication, which are common topics in the computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of identity-based encryption and group signature, which are topics in the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
